        body: "**Example 1: Fix Onboarding to Reduce 30-60 Day Downsells**\n\nDownsell analysis shows:\n- Peak downsell window: Days 30-60\n- Downsell reason: \"Feature gap - product doesn't have features I expected\"\n- Cohort rate trending up: Feb 10%, Mar 12%, Apr 14%\n\n**Root cause**: Enterprise onboarding is weak. Customers don't discover key features; they assume the features don't exist.\n\n**Action**: Revamp Enterprise onboarding with dedicated walkthrough of advanced features (custom reporting, API, integrations, team collaboration).\n\n**Result** (May cohort, post-fix):\n- Days 30-60 downsells drop from 8% to 3%\n- Downsells due to \"feature gap\" drop from 33% to 8%\n- May cohort downsell rate: 10% (vs. Apr 14%)\n\n**Annual impact**: 12 cohorts × 5% downsell improvement × 20 customers per cohort × (€500 - €99) = €49,200 saved MRR annually.\n\n**Example 2: Introduce Mid-Tier Pricing to Capture Downgrades**\n\nDownsell analysis shows:\n- Downsell reason: \"Price too high\" (40%)\n- Downgrades are from Enterprise (€500) to Pro (€99) - huge gap\n- Gap size: €401/month. Many downgraders are likely looking for something in the middle\n\n**Action**: Introduce \"Enterprise Lite\" at €249/month (half of Enterprise, includes advanced features but fewer premium support/SLAs).\n\n**Result**:\n- Customers downgrading from €500 → €99 now downgrade €500 → €249 instead\n- Some of the €99 users upgrade to €249 (mid-tier becomes attractive)\n- Downsell from €500: Instead of losing €401/month MRR, you lose €251/month\n- Jan cohort: 3 downgrades from €500 → €99 becomes 3 downgrades from €500 → €249\n- MRR recovered: 3 × (€249 - €99) = €450/month (vs. €1,203 loss before)\n\n**Example 3: Segmented Retention Strategy Based on Downsell Drivers**\n\nDownsell analysis shows different drivers by segment:\n- Annual contract customers: 12% downsell rate, reason = \"need more flexibility\" (want month-to-month)\n- Monthly customers: 18% downsell rate, reason = \"price too high\"\n- Large teams: 8% downsell rate, reason = \"product change / growth\"\n- Small teams: 20% downsell rate, reason = \"price too high\"\n\n**Targeted fixes** (different for each segment):\n\n1. **For annual customers**: Offer \"annual with 1-month exit\" clause (gives them flexibility without month-to-month price premium)\n   - Result: 12% downsell rate → 7% (5 points lower)\n\n2. **For monthly price-sensitive**: Offer \"annual upfront discount\" (lock in 20% lower rate if they commit 12 months)\n   - Result: 18% downsell rate → 11% (7 points lower)\n\n3. **For small teams**: Introduce \"small team pricing\" at €199/month (€99 Pro tier, but for 1-3 people instead of unlimited)\n   - Result: 20% downsell rate → 12% (8 points lower)\n\n**Annual impact**:\n- Assume 100 customers per cohort, across segments\n- Downsell rate improvements: 5-8 points per segment\n- Weighted improvement: 6 points overall (18% → 12%)\n- MRR recovered: 6 customers × €250 avg ARPU = €1,500 per cohort\n- 12 cohorts × €1,500 = €18,000 annual MRR saved\n\n**Without downsell analysis**: You'd see NRR declining (78%) and assume \"churn is the problem.\" You'd focus on retention (getting customers to stay), not realizing the bigger problem is downgrades due to pricing and feature perception. The fixes (pricing tier, annual discounts, onboarding) would never be addressed."
